Poor Naomi was well off her game and Coco was on her's. Unfortunately we only got to see 1 hour and 7 minutes of match play. This is the problem with women's tennis as far as tennis fan's see it. Now consider the Federer Millman match, 4 hours of great tennis because of the different rules with the men's game. The women are getting off too light. They are professional athletes who are capable of playing the same rules as the men do. They virtually get the same money in prizes and no wonder the women's game plays second fiddle to the men's. Professional women tennis players are the luckiest female sports players in the world, one because of the amount of money in the game, and secondly, they know that they can go out and maybe only have to play 2 hours and 3 sets max.  Time for change I think...
